number.

@endnode

@node GetCmd "Included scripts/GetCmd.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}GetCmd.br@{ub}

   Displays the templates of all, one or a matching set of the THOR or
BBSREAD ARexx command sets.  Use "rx GetCmd.br ?" for help

@endnode

@node JoinConfs "Included scripts/JoinConfs.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}JoinConfs.br@{ub}

   This  arexx  script  is  ment  to be used when a conference changes
name,  and  you have both the old and new conference in your database.
It  will add all messages in the new named conference to the old named
conf.   Afterwards, the old named conference is renamed to the name of
the new named conference.

@endnode

@node Log2Info "Included scripts/Log2Info.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}Log2Info.br@{ub}

   Adds  the  contents  of  a  temporary  logfile  to  the Information
conference.

   Set  ConnectTHOR  of  Get/SendTCP  to  log to the file specified in
InfoLog.  If you also want the information logged to a permanent file,
specify the name in MainLog.

@endnode

@node PackData "Included scripts/PackData.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}PackData.br@{ub}

   This script will let you use the BBSREAD Arexx command PACKDATAFILE
from cli. See the BBSREAD documentation for @{"PACKDATAFILE" Link "BBSReadRexx.guide/PACKDATAFILE"}
documentation for further information.

@endnode

@node Reply2Enter "Included scripts/Reply2Enter.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}Reply2Enter.br@{ub}

   This  script  will  convert  all active reply events on a system to
enter msg events.  This can be useful if the remote system has changed
or packed conferences so that the events can't be sent as reply events
anymore.

   Replaces THOR:bin/Reply2Enter from previous 1.2x distributions.

@endnode

@node SetLastRead "Included scripts/SetLastRead.br"
@TOC Scripts

@{b}SetLastRead.br@{ub}

   This  script  will set the last read pointers for a ABBS system and
is  only useful on ABBS systems and conjuction with the supplied NComm
script.

@endnode

@node FSE_Commands "Command Reference/FSE"

ARexx commands in the FSE
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
 @{b}General Commands@{ub}
   @{" HIDE              " Link HIDE} Hides the editor
   @{" NOP               " Link NOP} Do nothing
   @{" QUIT              " Link FSE_QUIT} Quit the editor without any requester
   @{" REFRESH           " Link REFRESH} Redraw the window
   @{" REVEAL            " Link REVEAL} Bring back the editor after hinding it

 @{b}Status Commands@{ub}
   @{" CURRENTCHAR       " Link CURRENTCHAR} Returns the character under the cursor
   @{" FSESCREENNAME     " Link FSESCREENNAME} Returns the name of the screen this FSE resides on
   @{" GETFSEREVISION    " Link GETFSEREVISION} Returns the revision of the editor
   @{" GETFSEVERSION     " Link GETFSEVERSION} Returns the version of the editor
   @{" GETLINE           " Link GETLINE} Returns the contents of a line
   @{" ISFIRSTCALL       " Link ISFIRSTCALL} Returns first-call status
   @{" LINELENGTH        " Link LINELENGTH} Returns maximum number of columns
   @{" MAXMSGLENGTH      " Link MAXMSGLENGTH} Returns maximum number of lines
   @{" MSGFILENAME       " Link MSGFILENAME} Returns the filename of the file in the FSE
   @{" MSGLENGTH         " Link MSGLENGTH} Returns number of lines in this file
   @{" RECIPIENT         " Link RECIPIENT} Returns the receiver of the message you're writing
   @{" RECIPIENTADDR     " Link RECIPIENTADDR} Returns the receivers address of the message
   @{" SENDER            " Link SENDER} Returns the sender of the message in the FSE
   @{" SENDERADDR        " Link SENDERADDR} Returns the senders address of the message
   @{" SENDERDATE        " Link SENDERDATE} Returns the date and/or time of the message
   @{" CONFERENCE        " Link CONFERENCE} Returns the original conference of the message

   @{" XPOS              " Link XPOS} Returns cursor X-value
   @{" YPOS              " Link YPOS} Returns cursor Y-value

   @{" AUTOINDENT        " Link AUTOINDENT} Changes and returns the AutoIndent status
   @{" OVERWRITE         " Link OVERWRITE} Changes and returns the Overwrite/Insert status

 @{b}FSE Specific Commands@{ub}
   @{" BACKSPACE         " Link BACKSPACE} The same as a backspace-press
   @{" BEGOFFILE         " Link BEGOFFILE} Moves cursor to beginning of file (1,1)
   @{" BEGOFLINE         " Link BEGOFLINE} Moves cursor to the first char on the current line
   @{" DELETELINES       " Link DELETELINES} Delete a number of lines
   @{" ENDOFFILE         " Link ENDOFFILE} Moves cursor to the end of the file
   @{" ENDOFLINE         " Link ENDOFLINE} Moves cursor to the end of the current line
   @{" INCLUDEFILE       " Link INCLUDEFILE} Include specified or requested file
   @{" INSERTBUFFERLINES " Link INSERTBUFFERLINES} Insert a number of lines from the buffer
   @{" INSERTINPUT       " Link INSERTINPUT} Insert string asynchronously
   @{" INSERTLINES       " Link INSERTLINES} Insert one or more empty lines
   @{" INSERTSTRING      " Link INSERTSTRING} Insert string synchronously
   @{" INSERTTAG         " Link INSERTTAG} Ask THOR for a tag to include
   @{" NEWLINE           " Link NEWLINE} The same as a <return> press
   @{" PASTECLIP         " Link PASTECLIP} Paste clipboard contents at current cursor position
   @{" PLAYMACRO         " Link PLAYMACRO} Play macro number 1-20 asynchronously
   @{" SAVEFILE          " Link SAVEFILE} Save file to specified or requested name
   @{" SETPOS            " Link SETPOS} Move cursor to a specific position

 @{b}Requester Commands@{ub}
   @{" REQUESTNOTIFY     " Link REQUESTNOTIFY} Open a requester with text and gadgets
   @{" REQUESTSTRING     " Link REQUESTSTRING} Request a string from the user

@endnode

@node HIDE "FSE/General/Hide"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The HIDE command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Hide the editor.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   The next ARexx-command sent will wake it up again.

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   HIDE

@endnode

@node FSE_QUIT "FSE/General/Quit"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The QUIT command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Quit the FSE.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   Will quit without asking for confirmation to cancel the
   message.

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   QUIT

@endnode

@node REFRESH "FSE/General/Refresh"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The REFRESH command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Redraw the FSE window.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   REFRESH

@endnode

@node REVEAL "FSE/General/Reveal"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The REVEAL command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Bring back the editor after it has been hid with the
   @{"HIDE" Link HIDE} command.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   HIDE
   REVEAL

@endnode

@node CURRENTCHAR "FSE/Information/CurrentChar"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The CURRENTCHAR command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the character under the cursor.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   Remember that the command may return "".

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   CURRENTCHAR
   char = result

   REQUESTNOTIFY TEXT '"'char'"' BT '"_Ok"'

@endnode

@node FSESCREENNAME "FSE/Information/FSEScreenName"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The FSESCREENNAME command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the name of the screen this FSE resides on.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   FSESCREENNAME
   screenname = result

   REQUESTNOTIFY TEXT '"'screenname'"' BT '"_Ok"'

@endnode

@node GETFSEREVISION "FSE/Information/GetFSERevision"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The GETFSEREVISION command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the revision of the editor.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   GETFSEVERSION
   version = result

   GETFSEREVISION
   revision = result

   REQUESTNOTIFY TEXT '"''||'FSE version: ...
   '||version||.||revision'"' BT '"_Ok"'

@endnode

@node GETFSEVERSION "FSE/Information/GetFSEVersion"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The GETFSEVERSION command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the version of the editor.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   GETFSEVERSION
   version = result

   GETFSEREVISION
   revision = result

   REQUESTNOTIFY TEXT '"''||'FSE version: ...
   '||version||.||revision'"' BT '"_Ok"'

@endnode

@node GETLINE "FSE/Information/GetLine"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The GETLINE command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   LINENUMBER

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the contents of a line.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   Returns the contents of the line number given on the
   commandline, or the current one if none specified.

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   If there are no lines in the message, or the line
   requested is out of range.

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   /* Output contents of current line */

   GETLINE
   say result

   /* Output contents of line number 10 */

   GETLINE 10
   say result

@endnode

@node ISFIRSTCALL "FSE/Information/IsFirstCall"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The ISFIRSTCALL command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Determine whether this is the first time the editor is
   called on this message.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   Returns:
   "ON"  : This is the first time the editor is called on
           this message (i.e. you may want to quote it.)
   "OFF" : Edit message etc.

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

   ISFIRSTCALL
   if result = "OFF" say 'This is NOT the first time ...
   this file is being edited.'
   else say 'This IS the first time this file is being ...
   edited.'

@endnode

@node LINELENGTH "FSE/Information/LineLength"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The LINELENGTH command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
        Return the number of characters in the current line.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
   options results
   address 'THOR_FSE.01'

        LINELENGTH
   say 'This line is '||result||' characters long.'

@endnode

@node MAXMSGLENGTH "FSE/Information/MaxMSGLength"
@TOC FSE_Commands

@{u}The MAXMSGLENGTH command@{uu}

@{b}Template:@{ub}
   ,

@{b}Purpose:@{ub}
   Return the maximum number of lines in the FSE.

@{b}Specifications:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Result:@{ub}
   Will return 0 on success and 10 on failure.

@{b}Warning:@{ub}
   -

@{b}Example:@{ub}
